cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with computer vision and pattern recognition applications, specifically for handwritten Chinese character recognition. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an enhancement of the DCNN approach by incorporating domain-specific knowledge, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. The paper also involves feature extraction and classification, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL), making them possible sub-categories as well.
